<subSubSection id="CBBAA3A06BBD5C37AD8FB05EC27E497D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph id="AA4CFD18B93F9EDD266F924F72B855E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E771F5DD1C41D1CCF5D4B08EA32F4A55" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="EF47CE63E1AE8523572E9E7614F66906" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Areoda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Areoda maculata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="6357F8A591CA4B3FBDD89FD32F314CA6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Areoda maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gory, 1833.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DFECDC6C301D5CF19265EC1A461387DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="species">
<paragraph id="FEE8F1B75E7543F66A455F9B360AF8FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E73BA05F6B6A7DB1756E20F44EEB4C34" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4 species; length 12-16 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B828ED06880258650A030C7ED71B6D8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
On first glance, the Brazilian Atlantic Coastal forest endemic genus 
<taxonomicName id="14AA4B8D865CCEC5A7A5E4778C2B8C18" authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Parhoplognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parhoplognathus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9D867FCE76D8BDA9914F26F7FCCF8656" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Parhoplognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears similar to areodine leaf chafers such as 
<taxonomicName id="F8F6F69357E9603EEC62FFD7FA5C5286" authorityName="Macleay" authorityYear="1819" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Areoda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Areoda" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33DD11A4137682B4E06017C4C2AEB21C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Areoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
MacLeay or 
<taxonomicName id="98EEDB7C55542CD64FF594944B86218B" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrsopolis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Byrsopolis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FB9B4A13455AABFC000C360198A30779" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Byrsopolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Burmeister due to their strongly convex form (in lateral view) and the apex of the metatibia that possesses many spinules. However, whereas areodine chafers possess a complete frontoclypeal suture, species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="08DD395EC73980BB306EEBC35DA1EECA" authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Parhoplognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parhoplognathus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C1161FC60BD04681A796EF40F4DEB25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Parhoplognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an obsolete frontoclypeal suture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AADD66BDA527F5038BC2FE81457AA12E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="7235C24ACFD831B361FE11291D88CE65" author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B286" refString="Ohaus, F, 1934b. Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T.1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199A: 1-172." title="Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T. 1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199 A: 1 - 172." year="1934 b">Ohaus (1934b)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4DF766CFDE4ADC6904E5D72AC340B409" baseAuthorityName="Ohaus" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Chipita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chipita mexicana" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis id="206054BD0DF8B157005D23CA3C27065A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chipita mexicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to be a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="70E233031FE34116F9C6F0574009B9B4" authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Parhoplognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parhoplognathus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="499ACDFFAD74F39B9C13370138E122E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Parhoplognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but several morphological characters (in addition to the disjunct distribution) provide rationale for the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="1B34F5294C9711CEEC2C3395D6D091C2" authorityName="Soula" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Chipita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chipita" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="609F59F161A77BA40559EF0B92E5AA8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chipita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genera 
<emphasis id="82312ED912B4409946F9B5FE4727A14A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="78EEC39266C4501FC5DC5152D6379583" authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Parhoplognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parhoplognathus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Parhoplognathus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EC10AB9419ED87EEACE72A4D48CA3B83" authorityName="Soula" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Chipita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chipita" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chipita</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="ACB3AB9E013E411C873DEADDB349A423" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Platyrutela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyrutela" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87B0B8D8445FD5131CC1E149C744F187" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Platyrutela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(an anticheirine leaf chafer) share several similarities, and phylogenetic analyses could examine this overlap.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="37EA277490EB4D9895208D3CAA7245E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="EF56CA673E1D0E15B0EC9037FCF2E2D7" authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Parhoplognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parhoplognathus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1D01EC7A97CFC9135FA668F7F71B20FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Parhoplognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are diagnosed by the following characters: pronotum with apical bead obsolete or lacking medially; clypeal apex quadrate, reflexed, with or without emargination; external edge of protibia with 3 teeth; all claws simple (shared with 
<taxonomicName id="49DE5DD03713511349FA1F69253615D9" authorityName="Soula" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Chipita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chipita" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5D784B920977C20CCA0AC931249F8097" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chipita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DE8ACDDF97ECDD3568C8392F58C04368" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Platyrutela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyrutela" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2EF888B39CA46A8EC4F95474DC4C4C62" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Platyrutela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); mandibular palp with horizontal/longitudinal sulcus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A387289018817FD8C6A89D596D4EAEEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A synopsis of the species in the genus was provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EEEDD293121E96F1B5C809166659F0F1" author="Soula, M" journalOrPublisher="AECFT, Saintry" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B359" refString="Soula, M, 2008. Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale. AECFT, Saintry" title="Les Coleopteres du Nouveau Monde. Volume 2: Rutelini 2. Revision des Pelidnotina 2. Revision des genres: Parhoplognathus, Chipita n. gen., Heteropelidnota, Homothermon, Hoplopelidnota, Mesomerodon, Mecopelidnota, Patatra n. gen. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Rutelinae, Rutelini). Besoiro: Supplement au Bulletin de liaison de l'Association Entomologique pour la Connaissance de la Faune Tropicale." year="2008">Soula (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, but identification key, natural history, and general distributional information were omitted. Natural history, larvae, and sister-group relationships have not been examined for any species in the genus.
</paragraph>
